    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.3A+B: \"PHD2 Expression and Silencing in Dendritic Spines\"\n- \"IB showed that PHD2 was broadly present, including in synaptosomes and PSDs (Figure 3A). Using an antibody specific for PHD2 in immunostainings (Figures S4D-S4H), PHD2 was detected in neurites and dendritic protrusions of MHNs (Figure 3B) and rat hippocampal neurons (RHNs) (data not shown), in close apposition to synaptophysin+ puncta, suggesting postsynaptic localization. A wide distribution was also obtained in MHNs transfected with YFP-tagged PHD2 (PHD2WTYFP) (Figure S4I).\". Experimental description: - \"We prepared postsynaptic density (PSD) fractions from 2-week-old wild-type (WT) mice\"\n- Dissociated cultures are of rat and mouse species (both were tested and reported to give comparable results)",
